    <h1 class="text-3xl font-semibold mb-6">The Open Access Button browser extension has shut down</h1>

    <div class="max-w-[75ch] text-lg">
      <p class="leading-relaxed mb-4">
        As of November 18th 2025, the Open Access Button and its browser extensions for Chrome and Firefox are no longer supported. If you still have the extension installed, please remove it from your browser.
      </p>

      <h2 class="font-semibold mt-8 mb-3 text-xl">How to uninstall</h2>

      <div class="mb-6 leading-relaxed">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-lg mt-4 mb-2">In Chrome</h3>
        <p>
          Open your extensions page by typing or pasting
          <code class="bg-neutral-200 px-1 py-0.5 rounded text-sm">chrome://extensions</code>
          into the address bar, then find “Open Access Button” and click <strong><em>Remove</em></strong>.
        </p>

        <h3 class="font-semibold text-lg mt-6 mb-2">In Firefox</h3>
        <p>
          Open your add-ons page by typing or pasting
          <code class="bg-neutral-200 px-1 py-0.5 rounded text-sm">about:addons</code>
          into the address bar, find “Open Access Button”, click the three dots, and select <strong><em>Remove</em></strong>.
        </p>
      </div>

      <hr class="mb-6">

      <p class="leading-relaxed mb-4">
